lenders.name: Karen
lenders.loan_because: I want to make a difference in women's lives. I recently read a book called "Half the Sky" where I learned about the oppression of women around the world. I was shocked by the tragedies of sex trafficking, "honor" killings, and domestic violence that still exist everywhere. And I was moved by the resilience and power of women around the world as they stand up for human rights. I feel very fortunate to be living the life that I have. There is no way you can read a book like "Half the Sky", learn about the oppression and inequalities that still exist in this "modern" world, and not be moved to action. Microfinance is one way to empower women to start their own businesses and make an income. This money can be used to send their children to school, pay for hospital visits, and improve lives in general.
